                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Lets start with a 50% uptime group in OoW.  That is pretty decent overall -- not frenzied pulling, but not a yawnfest.  (uptime includes bio breaks remember)
<br />

<br />
You are an enchanter.  Now, do you charm or do you use your animation/nukes?
<br />

<br />
Lets start out with nukes and animation.
<br />

<br />
Your nukes give 6 to 8 damage:mana.
<br />
You regenerate 70 to 80 mana/tick.  Or, 70 to 80 mana for every 3 seconds of combat (50% uptime).
<br />

<br />
That's 140 to 213 sustained DPS.
<br />

<br />
The nice new animation we get in OoW does 60 DPS or so.
<br />

<br />
Thus, by nuking + pet, you can manage 200 to 273 DPS.
<br />

<br />
Alright.  Now, in order for a charmed pet to match this, it needs 1.5 times that DPS -- the pet eats 1/3 the DPS it does in XP.
<br />

<br />
So, a charmed pet that is a good replacement for nuke+animation has to do 300 to 410 DPS.
<br />

<br />
That's a pretty high end pet.  OoW pets do 3 to 5 times their DPS on charm breaks compared to while charmed, at least at higher levels.
<br />

<br />
So, this pet does 900 to 2050 DPS to the enchatner when charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
In other worse, to beat nuke+animation, you need to have a pet that does Tipt/Vxed style DPS on a charm break.
<br />

<br />
We have a choice.  For the same net xp benefit, we can either
<br />
A&gt; /pet attack, nuke.
<br />
or
<br />
B&gt; Charm a pet, buff them to the point that they do group-killing DPS on charm breaks, and rely on your group to keep you alive.
<br />

<br />
Note that these two choices are xp-neutral.  They both generate the same XP over time.  Which seems utterly idiotic?
<br />

<br />
The OOW charm nerf makes tipt/vxed-level danger pets a worse choice than nuking and using your animation.
<br />

<br />
Pets less dangerous that tipt/vxed level pets are worse than nuke+animation because they generate less XP-DPS and still consume your attention.  Until you drop down to a pet that is trivial to control (ie, unhasted/geared), which do about 100-150 DPS charmed.  100 DPS * 2/3 = 66 DPS, about the same DPS as our animation.
<br />

<br />
Now, quick question: which is less of a pain, a mob that breaks charm and beats on you for 200-500 DPS every 5 or so minutes (randomly), or an animation?
<br />

<br />
It is possible my math is wrong.  But as far as I can tell, only a fool would use charm in OoW in a group.  Did I make a mistake?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
