                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The amount the pet takes in XP is exactly purportional to the DPS the pet does.  1/3 of the DPS the pet does is "cancelled" for xp purposes.
<br />

<br />
So a pet that does 300 DPS is the same, XP-wise, to doing 200 DPS nuking.
<br />

<br />
The 1/3 of 1/3 estimates above are bad estimates.  You can only know what fraction of the mobs hps you do by knowing the groups DPS and the pet's DPS.  By simply scaling the pet's DPS into "xp DPS" the problem is abstracted away.
<br />

<br />
I am attempting to show that charmed pets do not speed up your XP rate in a group in OoW, while they significantly increase the danger to the group and make you an unreliable slower.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
