<br />
Necros are also a pretty opportunistic class. They can do damage with pet/dots, but they can also heal hp/mana for others. Sure you wouldn't want to use one as primary healer in a group, but they can do patch healing almost anywhere or dump mana and they always have the option of using a pet or doting. So how come we end up doing nothing at times when other classes have options?
<br />

<br />
I remember somewhere reading that sony doesn't consider our animations as pets so they're out (we don't get pet hold anyway even with our animation commands). And I can't really compare our nukes to other int caster's because we only have magic resist based nukes and there's a recast time on ours. Most other int casters get damage spells based on at least 2 different resists and don't have to wait 20 seconds before they can cast them again. So that pretty much leaves us being the illusionist class- oh wait. I forgot, we haven't gotten any new illusions really for the last 3 expansions or so I believe.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_evil.gif" alt="icon_evil.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
